### Development Mode (Using Local Framework)

When developing the osprey framework itself (not just your application), use the `--dev` flag to install your local osprey version into containers instead of the PyPI version:

```bash
# Stop services
framework deploy down

# Deploy with local osprey framework
framework deploy up --dev

# This will:
# - Build a wheel from your local osprey source
# - Install it in containers, overriding PyPI version
# - Enable testing of framework changes immediately
```

**Prerequisites for --dev mode:**
```bash
# Install the Python build module (one-time setup)
uv pip install build
# OR
pip install build
```

**When to use --dev:**
- Testing changes to osprey framework code
- Testing unreleased osprey features
- Debugging framework issues

**When NOT to use --dev:**
- Normal application development (default mode is fine)
- Production deployments (always use PyPI releases)

